ZH: 我小时候常常放风筝。
EN: I used to fly kites often when I was a child.

ZH: 他很擅长制作风筝。
EN: He is very good at making kites.

ZH: 昨天我在公园里看到一个风筝比赛。
EN: Yesterday, I saw a kite competition at the park.

ZH: 我的风筝线断了，我需要买新的。
EN: My kite string broke, I need to buy a new one.

ZH: 开始放风筝时，你要小心电线杆。
EN: Be careful of the electric poles when you start flying the kite.

ZH: 风筝高高地飞在天空中。
EN: The kite flies high up in the sky.

ZH: 爸爸帮我系好了风筝线。
EN: Dad helped me tie the kite string securely.

ZH: 风筝断了线，飞走了。
EN: The kite broke loose and flew away.

ZH: 我的风筝被树枝绊住了。
EN: My kite got stuck in the tree branches.

ZH: 弟弟在公园里放风筝，我在旁边看。
EN: My younger brother flies the kite in the park, and I watch beside him.

ZH: 我买了一种特别漂亮的风筝。
EN: I bought a very beautiful kite.

ZH: 风筝线缠在一起了，我们得解开它们。
EN: The kite strings got tangled, we need to untangle them.

ZH: 风筝如何在空气中飞翔是很有技巧的。
EN: There is a technique to how a kite flies in the air.

ZH: 风筝会随风而动。
EN: The kite moves with the wind.

ZH: 这只风筝是我亲手做的。
EN: I made this kite with my own hands.

ZH: 风筝的尾巴很长。
EN: The kite has a long tail.

ZH: 风筝的线应该要拉紧。
EN: The kite string should be pulled tight.

ZH: 孩子们在田野上快乐地放着风筝。
EN: The children joyfully fly kites in the field.

ZH: 风筝向上冲破云彩。
EN: The kite soars up through the clouds.

ZH: 我的风筝不小心撞到了一棵树。
EN: My kite accidentally hit a tree.
